n\nReturn *the **number of different orders** you can build all the rooms in*. Since the answer may be large, return it **modulo** `10⁹ + 7`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1916-count-ways-to-build-rooms-in-an-ant-colony/1916-d1.JPG]]\n\nInput: prevRoom = [-1,0,1]\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: There is only one way to build the additional rooms: 0 → 1 → 2\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1916-count-ways-to-build-rooms-in-an-ant-colony/1916-d2.JPG]]\n\n**\n\nInput: prevRoom = [-1,0,0,1,2]\nOutput: 6\nExplanation:\nThe 6 ways are:\n0 → 1 → 3 → 2 → 4\n0 → 2 → 4 → 1 → 3\n0 → 1 → 2 → 3 → 4\n0 → 1 → 2 → 4 → 3\n0 → 2 → 1 → 3 → 4\n0 → 2 → 1 → 4 → 3\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `n == prevRoom.length`\n\n- `2 <= n <= 10⁵`\n\n- `prevRoom[0] == -1`\n\n- `0 <= prevRoom[i] < n` for all `1 <= i < n`\n\n- Every room is reachable from room `0` once all the rooms are built.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/count-ways-to-build-rooms-in-an-ant-colony/","problemName":"Count Ways to Build Rooms in an Ant Colony","problemNumber":1916,"problemSlug":"count-ways-to-build-rooms-in-an-ant-colony","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1916,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Database"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Table: `Listens`","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"+-------------+---------+\n| Column Name | Type    |\n+-------------+---------+\n| user_id     | int     |\n| song_id     | int     |\n| day         | date    |\n+-------------+---------+\nThis table may contain duplicates (In other words, there is no primary key for this table in SQL).\nEach row of this table indicates that the user user_id listened to the song song_id on the day day.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Table: `Friendship`","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"+---------------+---------+\n| Column Name   | Type    |\n+---------------+---------+\n| user1_id      | int     |\n| user2_id      | int     |\n+----