lutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Hash Table","String"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"There is a malfunctioning keyboard where some letter keys do not work. All other keys on the keyboard work properly.\n\nGiven a string `text` of words separated by a single space (no leading or trailing spaces) and a string `brokenLetters` of all **distinct** letter keys that are broken, return *the **number of words** in* `text` *you can fully type using this keyboard*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: text = \"hello world\", brokenLetters = \"ad\"\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: We cannot type \"world\" because the 'd' key is broken.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: text = \"leet code\", brokenLetters = \"lt\"\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: We cannot type \"leet\" because the 'l' and 't' keys are broken.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: text = \"leet code\", brokenLetters = \"e\"\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: We cannot type either word because the 'e' key is broken.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= text.length <= 10⁴`\n\n- `0 <= brokenLetters.length <= 26`\n\n- `text` consists of words separated by a single space without any leading or trailing spaces.\n\n- Each word only consists of lowercase English letters.\n\n- `brokenLetters` consists of **distinct** lowercase English letters.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Hash Table","String"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"There is a malfunctioning keyboard where some letter keys do not work. All other keys on the keyboard work properly.\n\nGiven a string `text` of words separated by a single space (no leading or trailing spaces) and a string `brokenLetters` of all **distinct** letter keys that are broken, return *the **number of words** in* `text` *you can fully type using this keyboard*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: text = \"hello world\", brokenLetters = \"ad\"\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: We cannot type \"world\" because the 'd' key is broken.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: text = \"leet code\", brokenLetters = \"lt\"\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: We cannot type \"leet\" because the 'l' and 't' keys are broken.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: text = \"leet code\", brokenLetters = \"e\"\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: We cannot type either word because the 'e' key is broken.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= text.length <= 10⁴`\n\n- `0 <= brokenLetters.length <= 26`\n\n- `text` consists of words separated by a single space without any leading or trailing spaces.\n\n- Each word only consists of lowercase English letters.\n\n- `brokenLetters` consists of **distinct** lowercase English letters.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-number-of-words-you-can-type/","problemName":"Maximum Number of Words You Can Type","problemNumber":1935,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"There is a malfunctioning keyboard where some letter keys do not work. All other keys on the keyboard work properly.\n\nGiven a string `text` of words separated by a single space (no leading or trailing spaces) and a string `brokenLetters` of all **distinct** letter keys that are broken, return *the **number of words** in* `text` *you can fully type using this keyboard*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: text = \"hello world\", brokenLetters = \"ad\"\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: We cannot type \"world\" because the 'd' key is broken.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: text = \"leet code\", brokenLetters = \"lt\"\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: We cannot type \"leet\" because the 'l' and 't' keys are broken.","