aximum-number-of-words-you-can-type","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1935,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Greedy"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **strictly increasing** integer array `rungs` that represents the **height** of rungs on a ladder. You are currently on the **floor** at height `0`, and you want to reach the last rung.\n\nYou are also given an integer `dist`. You can only climb to the next highest rung if the distance between where you are currently at (the floor or on a rung) and the next rung is **at most** `dist`. You are able to insert rungs at any positive **integer** height if a rung is not already there.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** number of rungs that must be added to the ladder in order for you to climb to the last rung.*\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: rungs = [1,3,5,10], dist = 2\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\nYou currently cannot reach the last rung.\nAdd rungs at heights 7 and 8 to climb this ladder. \nThe ladder will now have rungs at [1,3,5,7,8,10].","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: rungs = [3,6,8,10], dist = 3\nOutput: 0\nExplanation:\nThis ladder can be climbed without adding additional rungs.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: rungs = [3,4,6,7], dist = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\nYou currently cannot reach the first rung from the ground.\nAdd a rung at height 1 to climb this ladder.\nThe ladder will now have rungs at [1,3,4,6,7].","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= rungs.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= rungs[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= dist <= 10⁹`\n\n- `rungs` is **strictly increasing**.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Greedy"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a **strictly increasing** integer array `rungs` that represents the **height** of rungs on a ladder. You are currently on the **floor** at height `0`, and you want to reach the last rung.\n\nYou are also given an integer `dist`. You can only climb to the next highest rung if the distance between where you are currently at (the floor or on a rung) and the next rung is **at most** `dist`. You are able to insert rungs at any positive **integer** height if a rung is not already there.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** number of rungs that must be added to the ladder in order for you to climb to the last rung.*\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: rungs = [1,3,5,10], dist = 2\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\nYou currently cannot reach the last rung.\nAdd rungs at heights 7 and 8 to climb this ladder. \nThe ladder will now have rungs at [1,3,5,7,8,10].\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: rungs = [3,6,8,10], dist = 3\nOutput: 0\nExplanation:\nThis ladder can be climbed without adding additional rungs.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: rungs = [3,4,6,7], dist = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\nYou currently cannot reach the first rung from the ground.\nAdd a rung at height 1 to climb this ladder.\nThe ladder will now have rungs at [1,3,4,6,7].\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= rungs.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= rungs[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= dist <= 10⁹`\n\n- `rungs` is **strictly increasing**.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/add-minimum-number-of-rungs/","problemName":"Add Minimum Number of Rungs","problemNumber":1936,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **strictly increasing** integer array `rungs` that represents the **height** of rungs on a ladder. You are currently on the **floor** at height `0`, and you want to reach the last rung.\n\nYou are also given an integer `dist`. You can only climb to the next highest rung if the distance between where you are currently at (the floor or on a rung) and the next rung is **at most** `dist`. You are able to insert rungs at any positive **integer** height if a rung is not already there.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** number of rungs that must be added to the ladder in order for you to climb to the last rung.*\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: rungs = [1,3,5,10], dist = 2\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\nYou currently cannot reach the last rung.\nAdd rungs at heights 7 and 8 to climb this ladder. \nThe ladder will now have rungs at [1,3,5,7,8,10].","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: rungs = [3,6,8,10], dist = 3\nOutput: 0\nExplanation:\nThis ladder can be climbed without adding additional rungs.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: rungs = [3,4,6,7], dist = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\nYou currently cannot reach the first rung from the ground.\nAdd a rung at height 1 to climb this ladder.\nThe ladder will now have rungs at [1,3,4,6,7].","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= rungs.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= rungs[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= dist <= 10⁹`\n\n- `rungs` is **strictly increasing**.","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Medium","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given a **strictly increasing** integer array `rungs` that represents the **height** of rungs on a ladder. You are currently on the **floor** at height `0`, and you want to reach the last rung.\n\nYou are also given an integer `dist`. You can only climb to the next highest rung if the distance between where you are currently at (the floor or on a rung) and the next rung is **at most** `dist`. You are able to insert rungs at any positive **integer** height if a rung is not already there.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** number of rungs that must be added to the ladder in order for you to climb to the last rung.*\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: rungs = [1,3,5,10], dist = 2\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\nYou currently cannot reach the last rung.\nAdd rungs at heights 7 and 8 to climb this ladder. \nThe ladder will now have rungs at [1,3,5,7,8,10].\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: rungs = [3,6,8,10], dist = 3\nOutput: 0\nExplanation:\nThis ladder can be climbed without adding additional rungs.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: rungs = [3,4,6,7], dist = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\nYou currently cannot reach the first rung from the ground.\nAdd a rung at height 1 to climb this ladder.\nThe ladder will now have rungs at [1,3,4,6,7].\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= rungs.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= rungs[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= dist <= 10⁹`\n\n- `rungs` is **strictly increasing**.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/add-minimum-number-of-rungs/","problemName":"Add Minimum Number of Rungs","problemNumber":1936,"problemSlug":"add-minimum-number-of-rungs","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1936,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":17276,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1937-maximum-number-of-points-with-cost/1937-screenshot-2021-07-12-at-13-40-26-diagram-drawio-diagrams-net.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/1937-screenshot-2021-07-12-at-13-40-26-diagram-drawio-diagrams-net.png","sha256":"87f323ed2eb5333b1af9e6a8f0d3a3c88e51f7f78eae13c5444b7e419c7b9cfa"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":13413,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1937-maximum-number-of-points-with-cost/1937-screenshot-2021-07-12-at-13-42-14-diagram-drawio-diagrams-net.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/1937-screenshot-2021-07-12-at-13-42-14-diagram-drawio-diagrams-net.png","sha256":"8b59cf65086efdf32953d9d95449038c2fad845df894d82147fb75cb240a2593"}],"categories":["Array","Dynamic Programming","Matrix"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an `m x n` integer matrix `points` (**0-indexed**). Starting with `0` points, you want to **maximize** the number of points you 